o: Website Rank (Page Rank) is Google’s algorithm designed to measure the importance of a webpage based on the quality and quantity of webpages that refer to it. Pages that have high PageRank (i.e., a large number of quality backlinks) are perceived as more authoritative by Google and rank better than those with lower PageRank.

o: Estimated Organic Traffic is an estimation of website traffic that can be driven by the group of keywords your website is ranked for. The metric displays the approximate number of monthly visits the keywords can lead to your website (this doesn't include traffic from other sources, only organic traffic). ETV is calculated by multiplying a keyword’s search volume by the click-through rate coefficient of a search result

ETV מחושב על ידי הכפלת נפח החיפוש של ביטוי במקדם שיעור הקליקים של תוצאת חיפוש

o: You can choose which columns to show, for example you can choose to see if landing page of the given keyword contains the keyword etc.

Click on the keyword to see more details, you can see the top 100 results, and also you can track your progress and see the previous ranks you had. You can also find Related Keywords and add them to your list

Add new Landing Pages to your list, if you added more pages to your website you can manually add those pages here, or you can also choose to rescan your website again and let us find the landing pages of your website.

Click on each Landing Page in the grid to see more details about the page, below you can see also tips and hints how to improve your landing pages, those recommendations are calculated in real time so you can also refresh the page test it again

Here you can see the overall score of your website, it is calculated by the number of warnings we found on your landing pages. By getting high score your website can get higher ranks in Google and then of course more traffic
